                    "body": "{quote}table and schema names are stored all uppercase in oracle anyway{quote}\n\nIn Oracle you can do this:\n{code}\ncreate table \"foo\"  (\n   \"bar\"  VARCHAR2(50)  not null,\n   \"baz\"  VARCHAR2(50)  not null\n);\n{code}\n\nBy requesting ALL_TAB_COLUMNS or ALL_TABLES, you will obtain in lowercase:\n{code}\nTABLE_NAME                     \n------------------------------ \nfoo\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mikaelkael",
